OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNurses speak Welsh to help 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fboy in English hospital    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A mother has thanked a student nurse   
OL,6, for writing comforting phrases in Welsh
OL,7, on the bedside notes of her son while  
OL,8, he was in hospital in Birmingham.      
OL,10,FNatalie Ridler, from Gorseinon,        
OL,11,FSwansea, said the nurse wrote down     
OL,12,Fphrases for colleagues to use to soothe
OL,13,Fher then-two-year-old son, Morgan.     
OL,15,FHer message said: "Mum reported that   
OL,16,Fspeaking Welsh to Morgan helps soothe  
OL,17,Fhim. Here's some that may help."       
OL,19,FMorgan was in intensive care after     
OL,20,Fhaving surgery to remove a tumour.     
